Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportIsolation(25.10)                                  reportIsolation(25.10)

Name
       reportIsolation  -  Reports  or shows the added isolation cells and in-
       stances

Syntax
       reportIsolation

       [-help]

       [-highlight]

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       [-from <powerDomain>]

       [-to <powerDomain>]

       Reports or shows the added isolation cells and instances.

       Note: Use this command after you add isolation cells.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each reportIsolation parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man reportIsolation.

       -from  Reports all the isolation instances connected to the output pins
              of the power domain specified in -from option.

              Default: Reports all isolation cells.

       -highlight
              Highlights isolation instances in the main window.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Writes isolation cell and instance names to a report.

              Default: The software writes the report to a default file:  <de-
              signName>.isolation.rpt

       -to    Reports  all the isolation instances connected to the input pins
              of the power domain specified in -to option.

              Default: Reports all isolation cells.

Examples
       The following command highlights isolation cells and  writes  the  cell
       names to isolationCellReport:

       reportIsolationCell -highlight -outfile isolationCellReport

Related Information
       Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

